Hello, 

I have an existing project using Bootstrap 3.3.7 and was using Fontawesome 4.7 until I attempted to upgrade to 5 today. The icons are currently rendering, but are causing a TypeError that's killing my page.

I'm doing SSR (using Pug), but including fontawesome in JS script:

```var fontawesome = require('@fortawesome/fontawesome')
var faBrands = require('@fortawesome/fontawesome-free-brands')
var faSolid = require('@fortawesome/fontawesome-free-solid')
var faRegular = require('@fortawesome/fontawesome-free-regular')
fontawesome.library.add(faBrands)
fontawesome.library.add(faSolid)
fontawesome.library.add(faRegular)```

and I'm getting the following error in the browser:
`Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read property 'icon' of undefined`

This seems to be causing the error (inside the js bundle):

```function define(prefix, icons) {
  var normalized = Object.keys(icons).reduce(function (acc, iconName) {
    var icon = icons[iconName];
    var expanded = !!icon._icon_ [this is throwing the error, icon.icon doesn't seem to exist];```

I'm using jQuery, but read https://fontawesome.com/how-to-use/svg-with-js#with-jquery. My `<i>` tags are all nested within `a` tags, and inspecting the DOM elements it looks like the svg replacement is happening fine and leaves the a tags intact. I do have a click listener attached to one of the a tags, but that shouldn't matter since the a tag isn't changed. 

Any ideas?

Currently, dynet do runtime checking on the forward/backward (dimension, input indices, etc.) at any circumstance. And the time consumption is non-trivial. I've tried blinding the LookupNode::forward by removing such checking (line: 257-258 in param-nodes.cc) and it led to less running time (8800+ ms to 8300+ ms on 1000000 lookups, code below).

It would be great to let the user decide whether performing runtime checking. In some circumstance, the user would be sure that their network's dimensions are correctly configured and everything is right with their data.

reference code:
```
  dynet::Model m;
  dynet::LookupParameter p_W = m.add_lookup_parameters(n_entries, { n_dim });
  for (unsigned i = 0; i < embeddings.size(); ++i) { p_W.initialize(i, embeddings[i]); }

  unsigned n_repeat = boost::lexical_cast<unsigned>(argv[2]);
  unsigned n_tests = boost::lexical_cast<unsigned>(argv[3]);
  unsigned n_batch = boost::lexical_cast<unsigned>(argv[4]);
  std::vector<std::vector<unsigned>> tests(n_tests, std::vector<unsigned>(n_batch));
  for (unsigned t = 0; t < n_tests; ++t) {
    for (unsigned b = 0; b < n_batch; ++b) { tests[t][b] = ((*dynet::rndeng)()) % n_entries; }
  }
  auto time_start = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
  unsigned t = 0;
  std::cerr << "start testing" << std::endl;
  for (unsigned repeat = 0; repeat < n_repeat; ++repeat) {
    dynet::ComputationGraph cg;
    dynet::expr::Expression emb = dynet::expr::lookup(cg, p_W, tests[t]);
    std::vector<float> v = dynet::as_vector(cg.get_value(emb));
    std::cout << v[0] << std::endl;
    t++;
    if (t == n_tests) { t = 0; }
  }
  auto eclipsed = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now() - time_start;
  std::cerr << "consume time: " << std::chrono::duration<double, std::milli>(eclipsed).count() << std::endl;
```

